narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: A discussion group with the eminent and encouraging Bloom. Read as intensely as you choose, and be prepared to be called upon to read and speak in class. He brings a personal knowledge of the poets, a comprehensive understanding of all of literature, and an astounding amount of care for his students. Take it!
I would recommend this class. The poetry is wonderful, and class with Professor Bloom is an experience worth having.
Of course you should take it. Class with Harold is a once in a lifetime experience. Unbelievable. Also, I think he's better on poetry than he is on Shakespeare.
Take it! You'll read modern poets you probably haven't read--turns out great poetry is still being written in our time. Awesome.
